      "writtenOn": "2020-09-21T18:37:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "grapheme\n\nthese should at least be named so it\u0027s obvious what\u0027s here. I wouldn\u0027t even mind (in fact it would be nice) if they were different types (SkUnicodeLineBreak, SkUnicodeGraphemeBreak, etc, could derive from an abstract SkUnicodeBreak if needed). That icu uses the same type with a enum to pick the kind of iterator is an implementation detail based on which data to run the same underlying algorithm over. The interfaces look the same, but the actual output between them isn\u0027t really the same. It would be nice to ensure they can\u0027t be mixed.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 646,
        "startChar": 33,
        "endLine": 646,
        "endChar": 34
      },
