    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "72fb16bf_b7268a65",
        "filename": "modules/skshaper/src/SkUnicode.h",
        "patchSetId": 15
      },
      "lineNbr": 70,
      "author": {
        "id": 5140
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-09-21T18:37:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I understand this is trying to factor setting multiple iterators to the same bit of text, but it\u0027s really ugly at the call site (oh, I\u0027m setting the text on \u0027this\u0027... and also \u0027those\u0027!?).\n\nI think the issue here is not having a UText like abstraction, which is useful for lots of things that SkShaper doesn\u0027t currently really support but really should, like the input text not necessarily being contiguous (most editors generally don\u0027t have all their text in a contiguous backing).",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 70,
        "startChar": 29,
        "endLine": 70,
        "endChar": 73
      },
